The book received positive reviews in ''[[The New Yorker]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/books/page-turner/neil-gaiman-reanimates-the-norse-mythsand-loki-once-again-is-the-most-alluring-character|title=Neil Gaiman Reanimates the Norse Myths—and Loki, Once Again, Is the Most Alluring Character|first=Katy|last=Waldman|date=19 March 2018|publisher=|accessdate=10 May 2018|via=www.newyorker.com}}</ref> ''[[Washington Post]]''<ref name="auto"/> and ''[[The Times]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/norse-mythology-by-neil-gaiman-cz8tj3h0p|title=Norse Mythology by Neil Gaiman|first=Laura|last=Freeman|date=10 May 2018|publisher=|accessdate=10 May 2018|via=www.thetimes.co.uk}}</ref> ''[[Kirkus Reviews]]'' called it "Superb. Just the thing for the literate fantasy lover and the student of comparative religion and mythology alike."<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/neil-gaiman/norse-mythology/ |title=''Norse Mythology'' by Neil Gaiman |date=December 1, 2016 |journal=[[Kirkus Reviews]]}}</ref>

